        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 3:04PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 303 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Walt Haring Snow Park, or 30 miles northeast of Crater Lake, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail. Hail could accumulate on roads. Heavy rain
could result in ponding and standing water.

SOURCE...Radar and road camera indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Roads may
become hazardous due to accumulated hail and/or standing
water.

Locations impacted include...
Chemult and Walt Haring Snow Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
